lead_paragraph: There are reasons to doubt whether a major Japanese drive will develop from the present brisk fighting at Kokoda in New Guinea. The enemy may wish to produce that impression, but it is more likely that behind the smoke of battle he is rearranging his defensive positions throughout the area.
